Patch: OSS Metabase's frontend selector returns the literal "Metabase"
instead of reading the `application-name` setting from the backend, so
the browser tab title and any other frontend caller of `getApplicationName`
shows "Metabase" regardless of our clj-side patch.

The selector is in frontend/src/metabase/plugins/oss/core.ts inside
`getDefaultSelectors`. Patch it to return "Tanuh".

If this patch fails to apply on a Metabase upgrade, find the new
PLUGIN_SELECTORS default for `getApplicationName` and re-anchor.

diff --git a/frontend/src/metabase/plugins/oss/core.ts b/frontend/src/metabase/plugins/oss/core.ts
--- a/frontend/src/metabase/plugins/oss/core.ts
+++ b/frontend/src/metabase/plugins/oss/core.ts
@@ -84,7 +84,7 @@
   getLoadingMessageFactory: (_state: State) => getLoadingMessage,
   getIsWhiteLabeling: (_state: State) => false,
   // eslint-disable-next-line metabase/no-literal-metabase-strings -- This is the actual Metabase name, so we don't want to translate it.
-  getApplicationName: (_state: State) => "Metabase",
+  getApplicationName: (_state: State) => "Tanuh",
   getShowMetabaseLinks: (_state: State) => true,
   getLoginPageIllustration: (_state: State): IllustrationValue => {
     return defaultLoginPageIllustration;
